{{Infobox dot-com company | name = Clipix.com | logo = Clipix logo.png | logo_size = 200px | logo_caption = | image = | image_caption = | language = English, French, German, Italian, Japanese, Korean, Portuguese, Russian, Spanish, Turkish, Chinese, Hebrew, Arabic | launch_date = {{Start date and age|2012|02}} | founder = Oded Berkowitz | parent = Clipix LLC | homepage = {{URL|www.clipix.com}} }}
'''Clipix''' is a [[Privately held company|privately funded company]] offering an online [[Social bookmarking|bookmarking]], [[file sharing]], and organizational tool.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://mashable.com/2012/07/12/clipix-bookmarking-tool/|title=This Pinterest-Like Bookmarking Tool Organizes Your Online Life|last=Bissram|first=Veena|work=Mashable|access-date=2017-10-27|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bitrebels.com/technology/clipix-the-tool-that-will-organize-your-life-like-a-ninja/|title=Clipix: The Tool That Will Organize Your Life Like A Ninja {{!}} Bit Rebels|date=2012-03-23|work=Bit Rebels|access-date=2017-10-27|language=en-US}}</ref> The utility is available in 13 languages, and as of 2014 had users in 154 countries.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://techcrunch.com/2012/06/27/clipix-wants-to-be-a-pinterest-for-the-real-world/|title=Clipix Wants To Be A Pinterest For The Real World|last=Lardinois|first=Frederic|work=TechCrunch|access-date=2017-10-27|language=en}}</ref> Clipix allows users to save [[Web content|online content]] and other documents to private or public "clipboards."<ref>Examiner.com, January 30, 2013, "World Travelers: check out the Clipix digital hub"</ref> By dragging a “clip” button onto the browser bar, users click and clip online items for later reference. Clipix users can also add [[Computer file|digital files]] they want to access, including [[Microsoft Excel|Excel]] spreadsheets, [[Microsoft Word]] documents, [[Portable Document Format|PDF]] files, and email messages.<ref>5mashable.com, July 12, 2012, "This Pinterest-Like Bookmarking Tool Organizes Your Online Life" http://mashable.com/2012/07/12/clipix-bookmarking-tool/</ref> To organize content further, Clipix also offers multiboards, which are created by dragging several clipboards into one "Main Category" clipboard.<ref>timesunion.com, March 29, 2012, "A Pinterest Alternative" http://www.timesunion.com/entertainment/article/A-Pinterest-alternative-3444965.php</ref> Syncboards are synchronized clipboards that multiple users can access and add to, in order to work collaboratively. The company’s "Price Drop Alert" allows users to name the price they’d like to pay for any item that is sold online. Once a "Price Drop Alert" is set, Clipix notifies the user when an item has been discounted to his or her preferred price.<ref>Golfdigest.com, July 12, 2012, "Shopping for Clubs? Planning a Trip? Clipix Might Be for You", http://www.golfdigest.com/blogs/the-loop/2012/07/shopping-for-clubs-planning-a.html</ref> The Clipix [[Mobile app|app]] for [[iPad]], [[iPhone]], and [[Android (operating system)|Android]] synchronizes with the Clipix [[User interface|web interface]].
Clipix is often compared to [[Pinterest]], a similar tool.<ref>TechCrunch, June 27, 2012, "Clipix Wants To Be a Pinterest for the Real World" https://techcrunch.com/2012/06/27/clipix-wants-to-be-a-pinterest-for-the-real-world/</ref><ref>mashable.com, July 12, 2012, "This Pinterest-Like Bookmarking Tool Organizes Your Online Life" http://mashable.com/2012/07/12/clipix-bookmarking-tool/</ref><ref>timesunion.com, March 29, 2012, "A Pinterest Alternative" http://www.timesunion.com/entertainment/article/A-Pinterest-alternative-3444965.php</ref>
